text: Mammillaria haageana is a species of cacti in the subtribe Cactinae. It is native to Mexico, where it is found commonly, and is widespread throughout much of the country. ==Gallery== Mammillaria haageana pm 2.JPG Mammillaria haageana ssp acultzingensis pm 1.JPG Mammillaria haageana elegans T139.jpg Guatiza - Jardín de Cactus - Lanzarote - J41.jpg ==References== ==External links== * Mammillaria haageana at Tropicos Category:Plants described in 1836 haageana
